text.tspan: Design Limitation
Working on a project of any kind will have limitations on the resources you can utilize
Time, Materials, Social Cost, Financial cost, environmental cost, space, and legal
1 – Time management is an essential component is successfully completing project.
It requires careful planning an continual revision and evaluation to ensure the project
stays on schedule. Effective time management involves preparing an action plan
which breaks the project into smaller sections. Time is one aspect of project that
cannot fully be control. A good time plan should account for time required by
other people to assist. Example being cosmetic
manufacture can be contracted to produce a bamboo snow product line.
2 – Materials are limited to some extent by the materials available, there are a number
of factors that must consider when selecting materials aka bamboo
a. Availability is a a major factor
b. Properties Bamboo have a vastly different properties and these properties need to be
understood so as to make the best selection. The end use of the material will be deciding f
actor in what is used
c. Price is always an important consideration. To be able to select the equipment/tools/etc
available to achieve the requirements aat the lowest price. Higher priced equipment/tools/etc
often have additional properties which may not be needed
3. Social Issues
4. Financial Cost
5. Environmental Issues
6. Space / location(s)= portable Containers –
Green house – Warehouse
7.Legal Issues – import/export, state/local levels,
patents, registration, branding must be considered
